 and Razarbag Police Headquarter. The slums, students halls and residential houses of common people were burnt to ashes. At 20 minutes past 12. that night Bongobonhdu made his announcement of independence and arranged for sending of this message of independence by wireless, telephone and telegram to every corner of East Pakistan. In the wireless message Bongobondhu said, This may be my last message; from today Bangladesh is independent... He was arrested that night at 1-30 by the Pakistan army and later taken to West Pakistan to be tried and kept in prison for his offence of declaration of independence Bangladesh.")),
